Figure 11: alpha diversity


(Fig. 11)
The alpha diversity in the Chromosol was more sensitive to elevated CO2 compared to the Vertisol. Over time the number of ASVs reduced and this was most significant in the Chromosol and at elevated CO2. In the Chromosol, lower ASV numbers after 3 days occured along with greater diversity (Shannon, InvSimpson and Pilou Evenness) but exclusively at elevated CO2 concentrations. At ambient CO2 no changes in alpha diversity were observed in this soil.

In the Vertisol diversity increased after 3 days under both, ambient and elevated CO2 concentrations but after 14 days the diversity under elevated CO2 maintained a higher diversity compared to ambient CO2.
